name: casa rural pikatzaenea de alquiler integro.
description: FOR POSSIBLE OFFERS or DISCOUNTS CALL THE OWNER Welcome to our house, an ideal place to disconnect, to rest. To sit on the grass and enjoy the usual good things. Friends. And the family, however big, because that's what we have the capacity to do.
neighborhood_overview:
The Bezi Valley is in the midst of nature, surrounded by mountains, countryside and lush forests. The humid Cantabrian climate makes possible a vegetation of great vitality and beauty that makes our valley a paradise for hikers and trekkers.

But Pikatzaenea is more than just a haven for walkers and mushroom hunters.

Our strategic location, in the region of Las Encartaciones, just 30 minutes from the centre of Bilbao, 60 minutes from Vitoria-Gasteiz and just over 90 minutes from San Sebastian-Donostia, makes us the ideal “base camp” from which to schedule various visits and excursions throughout the Basque Country: the Guggenheim museum, the hanging bridge of Portugalete, the Urdaibai Biosphere reserve, the historic centre of Vitoria-Gasteiz,etc.

Not to mention the many tourist attractions of LasEncartaciones, a region with a lot of history and a lot to see in very little space: medieval cities, caves, zoos and interpretation parks...

name: Apartment in Segura. Vasque country
description: Apartment wi rustic decoration in the second plant of a historical house (S. XVII). With capacity for 8 persons, it counts with a kitchen-dining room, lounge, two rooms with double bed, double one and a sofa bed. 2 baths. Garaje.
neighborhood_overview:
Village built on a hill at the foot of the Aratz-Aizkorri Natural Park and the Sierra de Aralar. Located in the region of Goierri, it has a beautiful and preserved historic center. It is one of the best preserved medieval villas that deserves your visit, both for its historical-architectural value and for its charm and cultural interest. At present this municipality has 1400 inhabitants.

During the Middle Ages, it was the capital of the region and was a refuge and a mandatory crossing point for all trade between the Ebro Valley and the coast ( Gasteiz, Agurain, Ordizia, Toulouse, Donostia).

Today Segura preserves splendid and beautiful stately homes and palaces of the time such as the Ardixarra house (Headquarters of the medieval interpretation center), the Lardizabal Palace (Current City Hall), the Bergara and Arrue palace, the parish church of the Assumption, the convent...

Segura, has different buildings that record that it was once a walled town.

name: Agradable casa familiar a un paso del mar
description: In Barrika, in an unparalleled location, close to the beach and cliffs and flysch, the villages of Sopelana and Plentzia and the metro to Bilbao is our family home,  a haven of peace  with a magical garden of 3000 m2 with fruit trees, palm trees...  A home decorated with mime and with all the comforts to enjoy it in winter or summer.
neighborhood_overview: Barrika is strategically located between the best beaches of Uribe Kosta and the beautiful village of Plentzia and the lively Sopelana. In front of the house passes a GR route that takes you walking along the Goierri to Plentzia, you can also walk to Sopelana where there is  a metro station that takes you to the center of Bilbao. It is 20 minutilllos (1.8km) walking , if you do not want to take the car there is no excuse! The beaches are accessible both on foot (20 min) on a beautiful route along the cliffs of the coast or of course by car.
host_about:
¡Hola!

Muchas gracias por tu interés en nuestras casas.

De vez en cuando, en época de vacaciones ofrecemos nuestra casa para alquilar y asi financiar nuestras propias estancias en otros lugares. Tambien solemos intercambiarla con familias de otras partes del mundo :) 
Tambien ofrecemos en alquiler nuestro apartamento de vacaciones en Portosin, Galicai un lugar llevo de recuerdos para mi ya que pase todas las vacaciones dude mi infancia. 
Esperamos que si elegís quedaros en alguna de nuestras casas paseis un tiempo estupendo y dejéis un pedacito de vosotros y vuestros buenos momentos en nuestro hogar

Muchas gracias!

name: Ondarreta-Palacio Real apartment, 50m from seaside
description:
The Ondarreta-Palacio Real apartment is newly renovated in full and is capable to comfortably accommodate 8 people. It stands out for its great luminosity and natural light as well as for its perfect location a few meters from the beach of Ondarreta and the Paseo de la Concha.
It is perfect for both families and groups, and it is fully equipped with everything needed to enjoy a relaxing stay and the cultural and gastronomic offer of San Sebastián. * Optional parking.
neighborhood_overview:
The location of the Ondarreta-Palacio Real apartment will allow travelers to enjoy one of the most beautiful and unique areas of San Sebastian.
During daylight, Matia Street is the traditional commercial hub of the neighborhood of El Antiguo, one of the most dynamic areas of the city of San Sebastian, where to find many traditional shops, stores, bars and restaurants. Another of the distinguishing features of El Antiguo is the nice walk from the gardens of the beach of Ondarreta until the Peine del Viento, the famous set of sculptures by Eduardo Chillida that has become one of the symbols of the city of San Sebastian. The old city center of San Sebastian is just ten minutes' walk, by the sea side, along the privileged Paseo de la Concha.
host_about: Soy una Donostiarra enamorada de mi ciudad y estoy encantada de recibir enseñar y compartir todo su encanto con visitantes que la quieran y la respeten tanto como yo. Aprovechar una casa estupendamente situada que, por motivos profesionales, yo no puedo disfrutar ahora, pero que seguro que algún día volverá a ser mi hogar!

description:
Recently reformed apartment located in the center of Las Arenas ( Getxo), close to the Puente Colgante, World Heritage monument. It also has the benefit of being really close to the beach zone. It takes over 20 minutes to get to Bilbao and surrounding areas ( Plentzia, Sopelana..).
Perfect location as it enables hosts to discover the essence of the Basque country.

neighborhood_overview:
Our apartment is located in comercial area of Getxo, close to Puente Colgante , World Heritage. You can find in the neighbourgh drugstores, supermarket, banks, pubs and restaurants.
It is close to promenade where you can find beautiful palaces. You can get Puerto Viejo in 20 min by foot, and also to the La Galea Cliff, a beautiful waterfront area.
Perfect location if you wish to visit the Basque coast: San Juan de Gaztelugatxe (appears in Game of Thrones), Oma fores, Lekeitio, Mundaka, Sopelana, Bermeo… It takes a 1 hour ride in car to get to San sebastián and Santander ( you can also get there using public transport). Vitoria is a little bit closer, over 50 minute ride, and the French Basque country is a little bit farer, taking 1 h 30 min to get there.

name: The Attic - Casco Viejo
description: Light and spaceous, this stylish appartment in the centre of the Casco Viejo – Old Town is a perfect base for families or friends wanting to discover Bilbao.
neighborhood_overview:
The Casco Viejo - Old Town is the heart of medieval Bilbao. This large pedestrian area has some of the best restaurants, museums, bars and boutiques you will find in the city and, undoubtedly, the best atmosphere.
The elegant Plaza Nueva, just 100 meters from the apartment, is a beautiful neoclasical square with traditional restaurants and bars. Every noon and evening you will see the locals enjoying a glass of wine and a pintxo while the kids run around. On Sunday mornings, the flea market offers the chance to find a small treasure.
Two great museums are right next to the flat. The Basque Museum, literally on the doorstep of the flat, offers a glimpse into Basque culture and history. The archeological museum will surely impress little ones with its whale skeleton.

The Guggenheim is just a 10 minute stroll along the river.
host_about:
Originally from Bilbao, I have lived for the last 20 years in Berlin, Oxford and Geneva. I work in a humanitarian organization and often travel to Africa for my work. 

My husband and I decided to purchase this little gem in Bilbao to have a base for our holidays with our two daughters. We would like to share our attic with friendly guests who want to discover Bilbao. 

My brother- Natxo  - will welcome you to the attic and help out with anything you need during your stay.

name: Piso en Bakio a 100 metros de la playa EBI-548
description:
Spacious and bright apartment just 100 meters from the beach, close to supermarket and surf schools. Garage in the building itself.
Ideal for beach, mountain, outdoor sports, nature, culture and gastronomy lovers. 8 min from San Juan Gaztelugatxe, 20 min from Mundaka (Urdaibai Biotope), 20 min from the airport, 25 min from Guggenheim Museum and Fine Arts.
It has 3 comfortable rooms and two full bathrooms. Living room, kitchen and rooms with access to a large terrace.
neighborhood_overview:
Gaztelugatxe (Rocadragon in Game of Thrones) is an islet in the town of Bermeo, but closest to Bakio. It is connected to the mainland by a two-arched bridge. On the island there is a hermitage dedicated to St. John dating back to the 10th century, although some discoveries date back to the 9th century. Along with another small neighbouring island, Aketxe, it forms a protected biotope, stretching from the village of Bakio to Cape Matxitxako.

The islet and its surroundings were the setting for some scenes from the seventh season of the HBO series, Game of Thrones, in which the beach becomes Rocadragón.

In the fiction of the series, you see a digitally recreated palace instead of an existing hermitage, but it does highlight the road with 241 steps that climbs to the top of the islet.

name: Camino del Norte
description: 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom home, free parking and WiFi, located near La Arena Beach and Itsaslur's Via Verde.
neighborhood_overview:
Pobeña is a district in the municipality of Muskiz, in the province of Bizkaia, Basque Country. To the west it borders Kobaron, to the south with La Rigada and San Julián and to the north with the Cantabrian Sea. It has the only natural beach of the entire Left Bank, the beach of La Arena, and on its cliff coast you can still see traces of its mining past, such as the mineral loading dock or various buildings that today are abandoned and in ruins.

Pobeña is included in the Camino de Santiago, within the Camino de Santiago de la Costa.

Next to Pobeña is a protected natural area, the Barbadun estuary, designated a Special Conservation Area (SAC) in the Natura 2000 network, and we also find the hermitage of Nuestra Señora del Socorro surrounded by oaks.

host_about:
Hola a todos!!!
Como veis me acabo de iniciar en el mundo del alquiler y trabajo con ésta página que me parece estupenda.  Soy muy detallista y me gusta que os sintáis como en casa, siempre os dejo alguna cosilla para cuando lleguéis cansados del viaje. 
A mi también me gusta viajar y encontrar una casa limpia y acogedora. Soy muy sociable y comunicativa, no tendréis problema en preguntarme sobre la zona o cualquier cosa que necesitéis.  Aún quisiera mejorar más,  acepto sugerencias.  Yo me dedico a cantar lírica,  la música es mi gran pasión y los libros. No puedo estar sin leer. Me apasiona la historia y recorrer sitios hermosos que tengan eso, mucha historia. Otra de mis debilidades son los animales, por eso acepto mascotas, porque para mí forman parte de una familia
Mi sueño es una autocaravana , algún día la conseguiré y me volveré nómada jj.
Espero que al llegar a mi casa estéis a gusto y no os falte de nada ( cosas de aseo, más ropa de cama y toallas y algún detalle que se me ocurra). Porque otra de las cosas que más me gustan es ver a los demás felices. Si yo puedo proporcionaros al menos bienestar, me sentiré bien.
Pues nada, a grandes rasgos, esta soy yo. Disfrutad de la estancia y del viaje. Viajar, aprender, tener curiosidad por las cosas o simplemente relajarse....eso es VIVIR.
Os espero !!!!

name: Cozy Room with Private Bathroom nearby the Beach
description: Comfortable bedroom with private study and bathroom in a fully remodeled apartment in the heart of San Sebastian. Located a 6-minute bike ride / 14-minute walk from the iconic La Concha beach and the historic center. Top restaurants, gastrobars, traditional pintxo bars, shops, markets, and the beautiful Buen Pastor Cathedral, a San Sebastian must-visit, are within short walking distance.
host_about:
Hi Traveler! 

- I am Andrea
- and I am Jose

We are a Basque-Colombian easygoing couple living and loving San Sebastian :)

- I grew up in this beautiful city, I am a "Donostiarra", which is how people from Donostia-San Sebastian are called. I run a startup of Artificial Intelligence applied to digital marketing optimization, I love walking around San Seabastian any random afternoon contemplating the trees, the ocean or the sunset, also love playing volleybol, eating and I'm an avid fan of cooking, decorating spaces and every now and then restoring an antique piece of furniture. I met Jose back in 2016.

- And I am a Colombian and Basque (by heart and choice) raised in Cali who moved to San Sebastian in 2012 to study my Bachelor's degree and couldn't resist to stay. I work in Food Technology Research an Innovation, love playing volleyball, eating what Andrea cooks and dancing salsa; I've had culinary training and experience in the past so I love cooking too ;)

We enjoy meeting new, diverse people, their culture, their lifestyle and hearing a couple stories with a glass of red wine, local sider, coffee or just water. Traveling is one of our passions; combining trips together and and each on their own we've visited: Colombia, Spain, Sweeden, Denmark, Finland, India, USA, Mexico, Chile, Argentina, Thailand, Vietnam, Malasya, Cambodia, South Korea, Jamaica, England, France, Germany, Portugal, Italy, Switzerland, Czech Republic, Dominican Republic, Canada, China, Marrocco and Israel. 

We have some good recommendations and spots for travelers to enjoy San Sebastian, including a pintxo-route and restaurant selection (curated by top chefs). You'll find the magic that this small, pretty city breaths and will enjoy its uniqueness, amazing food and landscapes very, very much!

name: La Concha Beach Seaview Room
description: Frontline seaview room in stylish apartment with expansive views to the bay of La Concha, the island, the Old Town and Monte Igueldo. You have use of the living room, kitchen and back terrace and there is an optional garage for your car.
host_about:
Hello! 

I am Lorea, and I am a journalist and athlete. 

I have also studied Iyengar yoga and I’m certified with Yoga Alliance USA as a 600 hour, Advanced Teacher across 3 disciplines.

I am Eurasian, a mix of 4 races. I’ve travelled to over 60 countries and lived in 6. 

Thank you for choosing to rent my homes.

Thank you for choosing to practice with me on the mat.

I look forward to meeting you.
